- **Structure**: container-config

## Usage

```bash
# Build image
docker build -t {{ app_name | lower }}:latest .

# Run container
docker run -p {{ port }}:{{ port }} {{ app_name | lower }}:latest

# Run with environment variables
docker run -p {{ port }}:{{ port }} \
  -e NODE_ENV=production \
  {{ app_name | lower }}:latest
```

## Multi-Stage Build Example

For production builds, use multi-stage:

```dockerfile
# Build stage
FROM {{ base_image | split(":") | first }}-{{ base_image | split(":") | last }} AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN {{ build_command }}

# Runtime stage
FROM {{ base_image }}
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist
{{ start_command }}
```

## Tags

- `latest` - Most recent build
- `v{{ version }}` - Versioned release
- `sha-{{ git_sha }}` - Git commit SHA
